# bin/logrun-tui-skiplist and bin/logrun-auto-functions are append-only
# cross-machine lists used by the logrun-auto widget. The first grows
# whenever logrun --auto detects an unknown TUI (alt-screen escape
# sequence); the second names zsh functions that should always be wrapped
# in `logrun --auto -c "$BUFFER"`. `merge=union-dedupe` (defined in
# git/gitconfig.symlink) does a 3-way union merge AND dedupes lines, so
# independent appends of the same name from two machines collapse to one
# after sync. resolve-by-attrs (script/bin/) reads the same gitconfig
# driver entry, so jj/sync_repo auto-resolves identically.
bin/logrun-tui-skiplist     merge=union-dedupe
bin/logrun-auto-functions   merge=union-dedupe
